                                       "settings":  {
                                                        "section_visibility":  "always",
                                                        "custom_liquid":  "\u003cdiv id=\"z05-twincore\" class=\"z05-feature-shell\"\u003e\u003csection class=\"z05-section dark z05-twincore-section\"\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"z05-wrap z05-grid-2\"\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp class=\"z05-kicker\"\u003eTwinCore Crossover Switch System\u003c/p\u003e\u003ch2\u003eNot a bass switch. Two ways to hear Z05.\u003c/h2\u003e\u003cp\u003eMost IEM switches feel like a small EQ nudge. TwinCore is different: it moves Z05 AuAg between two complete listening profiles, so bass weight, vocal position, treble air, and overall stage energy shift together.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eUse it like you would choose gain, filter, or cartridge flavor in a serious hi-fi chain: one position for warmth and immersion, the other for focus and bite.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"z05-actions\"\u003e\u003ca class=\"z05-btn\" href=\"#z05-order\"\u003eChoose your Z05 AuAg\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"z05-twincore-panel\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"{{ \u0027z05-auag-twincore-switch-closeup.jpg\u0027 | asset_url }}\" alt=\"Z05 AuAg TwinCore switch with blue and red position markers\" loading=\"lazy\"\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"z05-mode-grid\"\u003e\u003carticle\u003e\u003cspan\u003eBlue Mode\u003c/span\u003e\u003ch3\u003eWeight / Flow\u003c/h3\u003e\u003cp\u003eFuller low-end body, smoother upper harmonics, and a more relaxed center image for long sessions, vocals, jazz, pop, and immersive listening.\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/article\u003e\u003carticle\u003e\u003cspan\u003eRed Mode\u003c/span\u003e\u003ch3\u003eFocus / Spark\u003c/h3\u003e\u003cp\u003eTighter bass contour, more forward clarity, extra cymbal air, and a livelier edge for detail hunting, faster genres, and cleaner separation.\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/article\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/section\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cstyle\u003e.z05-twincore-section{background:#050505}.z05-twincore-section h2{max-width:760px}.z05-twincore-section p{color:#d8d1c7}.z05-twincore-panel{background:#111;border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.14);padding:12px}.z05-twincore-panel img{display:block;width:100%;aspect-ratio:16/10;object-fit:cover}.z05-mode-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:1px;margin-top:12px;background:rgba(255,255,255,.14)}.z05-mode-grid article{background:#0b0b0b;padding:20px}.z05-mode-grid span{display:inline-flex;margin-bottom:12px;color:#e2b768;font-size:12px;font-weight:900;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.08em}.z05-mode-grid h3{margin:0 0 10px;color:#fff;font-size:25px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0}.z05-mode-grid p{margin:0;color:#cfc7bb;font-size:14px;line-height:1.5}@media(max-width:700px){.z05-mode-grid{grid-template-columns:1fr}}\u003c/style\u003e",
